  <primary_outcome>
    <measure>fluid responsiveness</measure>
    <time_frame>1hr after arriving at ICU</time_frame>
    <description>ventilator peep setting was adjusted to 0cmH2O as baseline
Then peep was increased to 10cmH2O for 5 min.
We set peep to baseline 0cmH2O again, making patients to semirecumbent position following passive leg raising at 30 degree for 5 min.
After that, 300 ml of hydroxyethyl starch 130/0.4 was infused in the supine position for 10-20 min and haemodynamic variables including SVI were assessed 5 min after completion of fluid challenge.</description>
  </primary_outcome>
